!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

walk /wɔːk/

(walking,walked,walks) 

1. V-T/V-I When you walk , you move forward by putting one foot in front of the other in a regular way. 行走; 步行 

例： Rosanna and Forbes walked in silence. 罗莎娜与福布斯默默地走着。 

例： We walked into the foyer. 我们走进前厅。 

例： I walked a few steps toward the fence. 我向栅栏走了几步。 

2. N-COUNT A walk is a trip that you make by walking, usually for pleasure. 散步 

例： I went for a walk. 我去散步了。 

3. N-SING A walk of a particular distance is the distance that a person has to walk to get somewhere. 步行的距离 

例： It was only a three-mile walk to Kabul from there. 从那里到喀布尔只有3英里的步行路程。 

4. N-COUNT A walk is a route suitable for walking along for pleasure. (适宜散步的) 人行道 

例： ...a 2-mile coastal walk. …一条2英里长的海边人行道。 

5. N-SING A walk is a paved pathway. 小径; 走道 

例： She started up the walk toward the front door. 她踏上了通向前门的小路。 

6. N-SING A walk is the action of walking rather than running. 行走 

例： She slowed to a steady walk. 她慢下来，稳步行走。 

7. N-SING Someone's walk is the way that they walk. 步态 

例： George, despite his great height and gangling walk, was a great dancer. 尽管乔治身材高大，步态笨拙，舞却跳得好极了。 

8. V-T If you walk someone somewhere, you walk there with them in order to show politeness or to make sure that they get there safely. 陪伴护送 

例： She walked me to my car. 她陪我走到我的汽车旁。 

9. to walk tall→see tall

